In England, in the seven days to 23 January, there were 568,139 new confirmed cases (1,004.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 January, there were 550,899 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 3% (17,240 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 January is 13,895,065 (24,571.2 cases per 100,000 population).
